    "number": 15492,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[BugFix] Fix nightly MLA failure (FA2 + MLA chunked prefill, i.e. V1, producing bad results)",
    "user": {
      "login": "LucasWilkinson",
      "id": 8854186,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg4NTQxODY=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8854186?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/LucasWilkinson",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "For MLA chunked prefill we use `merge_attn_states` to compute the context for a chunked-prefill, this sometimes leads to 0 length contexts when regular prefills and chunked-prefills are mixed in the same batch. FA2 and FA3 have differences in what the return when the sum-exp is 0, (i.e. what to return for log(0) which is technically undefined), FA3 returns -inf while FA2 returns inf. The code was written for FA3, i.e. -inf (I think this is also just the more logical choice) resulting in failures when running on A100s that default to FA2. This PR updates `merge_attn_states` to handle both cases (easier and less error prone than trying to update FA2).",
    "created_at": "2025-03-25T19:08:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-03-26T03:33:22Z",
    "closed_at": "2025-03-26T03:33:22Z",
